{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":101002,"duration_api_ms":100358,"num_turns":16,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7b31c1d4-b385-4d10-99b7-006c6adebf5b","total_cost_usd":1.14136425,"usage":{"input_tokens":13,"cache_creation_input_tokens":87737,"cache_read_input_tokens":1019786,"output_tokens":3322,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":87737,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":13,"outputTokens":3322,"cacheReadInputTokens":1019786,"cacheCreationInputTokens":87737,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.14136425,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 108 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored) — verified by running cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","Amendment fr-18-38a5b058 FIXED: matching_finalized_task_runs (model.rs:448-479) now matches terminal entries by started_at when run_id is None, and record_task_run_start (fs.rs:2777-2808) calls this function before any running-entry check or new-row append. A runless start replay after completion is now rejected with 'already finalized' error.","Amendment fr-18-38a5b058 model tests verified: matching_finalized_task_runs_rejects_runless_replay_with_matching_started_at (model.rs:1080-1105) seeds a terminal entry with run_id=None and verifies it matches by started_at. matching_finalized_task_runs_falls_back_to_started_at_when_terminal_row_is_runless (model.rs:1108-1133) verifies fallback matching even when caller provides a run_id.","Amendment fr-18-38a5b058 integration test verified: replaying_a_finalized_runless_start_does_not_reactivate_the_milestone (service.rs:3044-3139) runs start→complete→replay-start, asserts 'already finalized' error, lineage has exactly 1 entry (Succeeded), snapshot remains Ready with completed_beads=1, and journal has exactly 1 start + 1 completion event.","Amendment fr-18-4380a444 (min finished_at): merge_attempt_entries (model.rs:324-329) still takes min of finished_at. This is consistent with the replay/repair design where the earliest completion time is the authoritative one.","Amendment fr-18-27c5623f (serde annotations): run_id, plan_hash, outcome_detail (model.rs:281, 284, 289) retain serde(default, skip_serializing_if). These are legitimately optional fields — run_id is absent for runless attempts, plan_hash may be unknown at start, outcome_detail only set on terminal entries.","Amendment fr-18-fdce56f8 (legacy collapse): collapse_task_run_attempts (model.rs) and related helpers remain active. These are load-bearing for the current NDJSON lifecycle where start and completion are separate rows that must be collapsed for queries and reconciliation.","model.rs: TaskRunEntry has all required fields — milestone_id (String, required), bead_id, project_id, run_id, plan_hash, outcome, outcome_detail, started_at, finished_at","service.rs: All mutation paths (update_status, persist_plan, record_bead_start, update_task_run) run under with_milestone_write_lock for serialized access","service.rs: reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage rebuilds counters from latest_task_runs_per_bead, preserves Paused status, transitions Active→Ready when no active beads remain, validates terminal invariants","All original acceptance criteria satisfied: milestone state answers 'what happened to bead X?' via find_runs_for_bead, controller can update linkage after each run outcome via update_task_run, no backward compatibility needed"],"findings_or_gaps":["AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs ~line 549) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run, which is semantically a finalization rejection. A more specific error variant would be cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior reviews.","The outstanding risk — milestone mutations span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction — remains. All paths are serialized by the milestone mutation lock and replay-safe, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","The active_bead_ids() function in model.rs:402-408 still contains its own internal latest_task_runs_per_bead() call while reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage computes latest runs separately. External callers of active_bead_ids would redundantly recompute, but this is minor and not a correctness concern."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"c0921c03-c48f-45dd-9e8b-5e564a4b8ddd"}
